        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 11:47AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1147 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Derma, or 13 miles southwest of Houston, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Houston, Vardaman, Derma, Pyland, Woodland, Tabbville, Sparta,
Anchor, and Atlanta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
